üîß Solution: Show Inline Validation Messages in InCell Mode
1Ô∏è‚É£ Still enable client-side validation like we already discussed:
[Required] in your model ‚úÖ

.Validation(v => v.Required(true)) in the DataSource model ‚úÖ

Add HtmlAttributes(new { required = "required", @class = "required-cell" }) ‚úÖ

2Ô∏è‚É£ Handle Save event instead of SaveChanges
Telerik actually exposes individual cell Save event ‚Äî fires after a cell edit.

We can hook into it to inject inline validation messages immediately.

‚úÖ Example:
JS:
javascript
Copy
Edit
function onGridCellSave(e) {
    var cell = e.container;
    var validator = cell.kendoValidator().data("kendoValidator");

    // remove existing custom validation message div (if any)
    cell.find(".cell-validation-error").remove();

    if (!validator.validate()) {
        e.preventDefault(); // cancel cell save

        // get validation message from the first failed rule
        var errors = validator.errors();
        for (var field in errors) {
            var message = errors[field];

            // inject inline error message under the cell
            cell.append('<div class="cell-validation-error" style="color:red; font-size:12px;">' + message + '</div>');
            break;
        }
    }
}
Hook into Grid Events:
csharp
Copy
Edit
.Events(events =>
{
    events.Save("onGridCellSave");
    events.SaveChanges("onSaveChanges"); // still keep full-grid validation here if needed
})
